<div id="review_3901470635" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3901470635" />
    <a title="Katja" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/118578359-katja"><img alt="Katja" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626563505p2/118578359.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3901470635?book_show_action=true">Jun 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Katja" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Katja" href="/user/show/118578359-katja">Katja</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140714692" href="/book/show/422874.Pericles">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=plays">plays</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=new-adult-and-adult-genre">new-adult-and-adult-genre</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=greek-history">greek-history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=standalone">standalone</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=adventure">adventure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=european-fiction">european-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/118578359-katja?shelf=secular">secular</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3901470635" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15590680727714680335">3 stars &amp; 3/10 hearts. This was an interesting play. I liked that Pericles was such an honest, moral/upright man, and quietly endured everything that happened without being warped, bitter, or wicked. Thalia was very good too. Marina was also very sweet. I didn’t find the plot very interesting, though… no big climax or anything, just the Happy Reunion™️ that reminds me a lot of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/82356.The_Comedy_of_Errors' title='The Comedy of Errors by William Shakespeare' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Comedy of Errors</a>, actually. The whole fact that there were several scenes set in a brothel and a lot of talk of pros</span>
  <span id="freeText15590680727714680335" style="display:none">3 stars &amp; 3/10 hearts. This was an interesting play. I liked that Pericles was such an honest, moral/upright man, and quietly endured everything that happened without being warped, bitter, or wicked. Thalia was very good too. Marina was also very sweet. I didn’t find the plot very interesting, though… no big climax or anything, just the Happy Reunion™️ that reminds me a lot of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/82356.The_Comedy_of_Errors" title="The Comedy of Errors by William Shakespeare" rel="nofollow noopener">The Comedy of Errors</a>, actually. The whole fact that there were several scenes set in a brothel and a lot of talk of prostitutes and of raping Marina bothered me a little, although nothing ever happens and people actually end up redeemed. I like the moral of bad people punished, good people rewarded, and redeemed people being blessed… I didn’t care for Diana’s interference though, haha. Overall, I feel like it was a mediocre play. Good message, okay characters, so-so plot… I don’t hate it, I don’t love it—I just kinda like it. Recommended age: 18+ for subject content. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15590680727714680335" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


